{{Quote|Serve me well, Toth, and you'll hold a prominent place in our New Order.|[[Count of Serenno/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] to [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Cavik Toth]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Starfighter]]''</ref>}}
The term '''New Order''' was used by members of the [[Separatist Council/Legends|Separatist Council]] and other Separatists to describe the vision of a decentralized, corporate-friendly [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] as represented by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. This contrasted with the use of the term "[[List of phrases and slang/Legends#O|Old Order]]" to represent the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. The idea of a separatist New Order was nearly eradicated when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] [[Battle of Mustafar (Imperial Period)|crushed]] the last [[Geonosian Industries/Legends|organized]] [[Separatist holdouts/Legends|remnants]] of the Confederacy and [[Imperialization/Legends|nationalized]] most of the cartels. However, the Separatist's New Order continued all the way to the [[Battle of Geonosis (Galactic Civil War)|fall]] of the [[Geonosis droid factories/Legends|Geonosis droid foundries]].

Whether the use of "[[New Order/Legends|New Order]]" by both the Confederacy and the Galactic Empire was due to them both being led by [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], or just coincidence, is unknown.

